Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Grate the @Cheddar Cheese{60%g}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the root from the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1}, halve lengthways and thinly slice. Zest and halve the @Lime{1/2}.

Drain and rinse the @Red Kidney Beans{1} in a #colander{}. Pop half the kidney beans in a #bowl{} and mash with a #fork{} until broken up.

== Beef ==

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium high heat (no oil).

When the pan is hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Drain the excess fat out.

Reduce the heat to medium and add the garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%g} and @Cajun Spice Mix{1} to the beef - add less spice if you don't like heat.

Stir to combine, then cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%mins}.

Pour in the @Water{750%ml} and add the @Beef Stock Powder{1}. Add the kidney beans (whole and mashed).

Stir until everything is evenly mixed and the sauce thickens. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. > Add a splash more water if dry.

== Dressing and Assembly ==

Meanwhile, put the @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} and @sugar{1/4%tsp} in a medium bowl.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and squeeze in the lime juice. Mix together until combined. Add the lettuce to the dressing and toss to combine.

Meanwhile, pop the @Plain Taco Tortillas{6} on the top shelf of your oven to warm through for ~{2-3%mins}.

Taste the beef mixture and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Serve the tacos with a spoonful of beef on top. Sprinkle over the cheese and lime zest. Add the lettuce to the tacos too.

Serve and enjoy!